Email sent to client: 

Good morning Saundra, 
It appears as though we are missing some documentation from your file: 
- Automobile Insurance Policy - We are not able to accept the insurance slip that you would've kept in the vehicle. We need the long form version with all of your policy information. If you do not have a copy of this, you should be able to request it from either your broker or directly from the insurance company. - Proof of Loss - This would have been one of the documents needed for your insurance claim. If you do not have this, you should be able to request it from the adjuster that was handling your claim. - Details of any arrears or penalties on the loan - The easiest document to obtain for this is a copy of the transaction history of all of the payments made toyour loan account. You should be able to contact the financial institution that holds the loan and they should be able to provide this to you. - KMs on the vehicle at the time of loss - This can be an approximate number, but should be relatively close to the actual Kms as it is taken into consideration when determining your settlement. 
Please let me know if you have any questions or concerns.
Thanks, 
Sarah Gabor
